This paper discusses epistemic planning, which involves decision making in multi-agent situations with distributed knowledge and capabilities. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO), as well as multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and planning (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper uses Dynamic Epistemic Logic (DEL), which is a type of modal logic that has been studied in the context of computer science and artificial intelligence, making cs.DL another likely sub-category.
